3. A 108◦ angle is bisected. What are the measures of the resulting angles?
Answers:
1.CB = BD by the Angle Bisector Theorem, so x = 6.
2. No because B is not necessarily equidistant from AC and AD. We do not know if the angles in the diagram are
right angles.
3. We know that to bisect means to cut in half, so each of the resulting angles will be half of 108. The measure of
each resulting angle is 54◦.
